Khosla Ventures Raises $1.05 Billion to Support Energy, Internet

-- B y   W i l l   W a d e
-- 
2011-10-13T21:36:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-13/khosla-ventures-raises-1-05-billion-to-support-energy-internet.html
Khosla Ventures, a venture capital
investor, raised $1.05 billion and formed a new fund to support
renewable energy and communications technology.  The Khosla Ventures IV fund will back early-stage companies
developing clean energy initiatives, wireless technology and
online systems, the Menlo Park-based company said today in a
statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Wade at 
 wwade4@bloomberg.net  